<div id="Idea_4106"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4106-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4106">Allow wealthy people to pay more taxes&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/9714-4049">melissa</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Don't raise taxes on the wealthy.  Let them pay more if they wish, and perhaps give them some form of tax credit for doing so.  Warren Buffet said he would be willing to pay more taxes and that the tax law should change as a result.  Why can't he just pay more anyway.<br/><br/>Other wealthy people may have a better use for their capital, like investing in new technologies that will lead to job creation.  So, wealthy people depending on their stage in life and activity can elect to augment their taxes with a greater payment depending on their attitude.<br/><br/>This is based on an economic concept of reservation price, that different people are willing to pay different prices for the same good, depending on the utility of that good to them.  Folks who want more government can pay for it.  <br/><br/>Post the contributions on the web, like universities do, to give credit to those that are more giving citizens.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_4106" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_4106', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2242&topicID=4106')">Comments (14)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_4106"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2242">New Strategies and Techniques</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=taxes">taxes</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_4106"></div>
