<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_4087"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4087-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4087">public outreach program to educate the public on "Constitutional Law 101"&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/9547-4049">dhein2000</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Who:  a public outreach team to develop educational materials and a plan to reach various age groups through various venues in order to make education available to the public on certain foundational constitutional principals so that topics that all branches of government deal with directly and on which certain campaigns are run can be understood more fully by people of all ages and backgrounds.  <br/>What:  A curriculum to include topics such as due process and privacy; review of the text of the constitution; discussion of landmark constitutional cases; discussion of the Federalist Papers and other primary sources of the Founding Fathers in order to establish discussion and further critical thinking.  Curriculum would be age and/or education level appropriate and would be made available through venues (to be decided by the team) such as classes made possible through local gov't and/or recreation programs, "enriched" public education curriculum for all grade levels including higher level education, as well as media outlets that allow for educational programming.  </div>
