<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/9294-4049">bethfurst</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">It is true that financial aid covers tuition and some living expenses. But often there can be upwards of 20,000 dollars of living expenses per year that needs to be covered, or more. I'd like to see a government program that covers this. It can sometimes be formidable to work and go to school, especially when available jobs are at minimum wage or 10.00 an hour. Bank loans are hefty. Perhaps the government could increase student loans to cover completely the cost of living. Or perhaps others have better ideas. Thank you  Beth Furst</div>
